│ stop({"edit_points": [[7513, 7528, "llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueTracking.cpp"]],   │
│ "thoughts": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe miscompile occurs when          │
│ InstCombine's foldSelectOfBools() replaces a select with an 'and' for boolean │
│ values under the assumption that this transformation is poison-safe. The      │
│ Alive2 check shows that the transformed IR produces poison in a case where    │
│ the original IR does not: when %c2 (icmp samesign eq %In, 1) is poison but    │
│ %c1 (icmp samesign sgt %In, -1) is not and is false, the original select      │
│ masks the poison, while the 'and' propagates it. The profitability/safety     │
│ gate relies on impliesPoison(TrueVal, CondVal). This incorrectly returns      │
│ true, enabling the fold.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe first transformation │
│ is select -> and (%V = select %c1, %c2, false --> %V = and %c1, %c2). No      │
│ other analyses (AA, etc.) are relevant; there are no pointers. The            │
│ transformation is triggered by foldSelectOfBools in InstCombineSelect.cpp.    │
│ The safety check used there is impliesPoison(TrueVal, CondVal) (or its dual   │
│ for the OR case). That function depends on ValueTracking::impliesPoison which │
│ in turn depends on canCreatePoison and isGuaranteedNotToBePoison.\n\n3. Root  │
│ Cause Analysis:\nThe impliesPoison logic incorrectly concludes that if %c2 is │
│ poison then %c1 must also be poison. This stems from canCreatePoison()        │
│ claiming that ICmp cannot create poison. That was correct historically, but   │
│ 'icmp samesign' changes semantics: an ICmp with the 'samesign' flag can       │
│ produce poison even if its operands are non-poison (operands with different   │
│ signs yield a poison result per LangRef 12404). Because canCreatePoison()     │
│ returns false for ICmp unconditionally,                                       │
│ isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(ICmpWithSameSign) may treat the compare as          │
│ guaranteed non-poison (after recursively checking operands), allowing         │
│ impliesPoison to incorrectly prove implications that are not valid.           │
│ Specifically, ValAssumedPoison = %c2 and V = %c1 share an operand (%In); the  │
│ framework over-approximates propagation because %c2 is (wrongly) treated as   │
│ never poison-producing, satisfying the recursive condition.\nThus,            │
│ ValueTracking lacks awareness that 'icmp samesign' can introduce poison,      │
│ leading to unsafe select->and folding.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nFile:   │
│ llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueTracking.cpp, lines 7513-7528 (the switch cases for    │
│ canCreateUndefOrPoison).\nChange the handling of Instruction::ICmp to reflect │
│ that an ICmp with hasSameSign() can create poison. We split out ICmp from the │
│ grouped case list and add a conditional:\n- If Kind includes poison           │
│ (PoisonOnly or UndefOrPoison) and the ICmpInst hasSameSign(), return true.\n- │
│ For ConstantExpr icmp, conservatively return true if poison is considered (we │
│ cannot query hasSameSign() on ConstantExpr; over-approximation is safe, may   │
│ only reduce optimization).\n- Otherwise return false (preserving prior        │
│ behavior for normal icmp).\nRationale: This updates                           │
│ canCreatePoison()/canCreateUndefOrPoison to correctly model poison creation   │
│ by samesign icmps, preventing isGuaranteedNotToBePoison from incorrectly      │
│ marking them as always non-poison and blocking invalid implications in        │
│ impliesPoison.\nAfter this change, impliesPoison(FalseVal, CondVal) in        │
│ foldSelectOfBools will evaluate to false for the reproducer, and the unsafe   │
│ fold to 'and' will not trigger.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy teaching ValueTracking  │
│ that samesign icmps may produce poison, we prevent incorrect reasoning in     │
│ impliesPoison which led to an unsafe select->and fold. This restores          │
│ correctness for the provided reproducer and any similar cases involving       │
│ masking poison with a select choosing a safe constant when the condition is   │
│ false. The fix is localized, semantically accurate per LangRef, and           │
│ conservative for constant expressions. Expected effect: the transformation no │
│ longer fires; Alive2 would then verify the remaining IR as correct."})        │
